This branch is for setting up git clones suitable for repo --mirror
aosp.xml			AOSP mirror manifest
create-mirror-manifest.py	Create evervolv mirror manifest
create-mirrors.py		Crap for manipulating manifests
ev_unique.xml			Manifest of evervolv projects not it aosp
evervolv.xml			Manifest created by create-mirror-manifest
README				This file
setup-combined-mirror.py	Create ev_unique from aosp and evervolv
				 if enabled will create symlinks for ev hosted aosp
				 projects and add remotes for ev,cm, and caf

to use:
	repo init -u https://android.googlesource.com/mirror/manifest --mirror

then:
	either:
		drop evervolv.xml into local_manifests
	or:
		drop ev_unique.xml and shared.xml into local_manifests
		this method will save some space and bandwidth as it removes
		the shared aosp projects

repos can then be init'd with the --reference option

to setup as dual mirror:
	COMMON=/opt/storage/git/android/mirrors
	cd $COMMON/aosp
	repo init -u https://android.googlesource.com/mirror/manifest --mirror
	cd $COMMON/evervolv
	repo init -u https://github.com/drewis/android_mirror -b jb-mirror -m evervolv.xml
	cd <path to build tree>
	repo init -u $COMMON/evervolv/android.git -b jellybean
	vim .repo/manifest.xml
	# replace fetch urls
	# aosp > $COMMON/aosp
	# github > $COMMON/evervolv
	(cd .repo/manifests && git commit -a -m 'use local clones')
	repo sync

